data.description: The annotate method is used to extract keywords within a posted text and optionally to link them to Linked Open Data resources by means of disambiguation. Linked keywords can be enriched with images, synonyms, DBpedia/Airpedia classes, categories, etc. Available in 5 languages: en, de, fr, es, it
data.name: Text annotation
abstract
data.description: whether to add abstract from Wikipedia (optional, requires “disambiguation=1″) 1 – enabled 0 – disabled (default)

data.name: category
data.description: whether to add categories from Wikimedia (optional, requires “disambiguation=1″) 1 – enabled 0 – disabled (default)

data.name: class
data.description: whether to add DBpedia/Airpedia type (optional, requires “disambiguation=1″) 1 – enabled 0 – disabled (default)

data.name: cross
data.description: whether to add links to other Wikipedia chapters (optional, requires “disambiguation=1″) 1 – enabled 0 – disabled (default)

data.name: disambiguation
data.description: whether to disambiguate identified keywords using Wikipedia (optional) 1 – enabled 0 – disabled (default)

data.name: form
data.description: whether to add alternative terms (e.g., synonyms) to identified keywords (optional, requires “disambiguation=1″) 1 – enabled 0 – disabled (default)

data.name: include_text
data.description: whether to include the original text into the response (optional) 1 – enabled (default) 0 – disabled

data.name: lang
data.description: text language (optional, must be a ISO 639-1 two-letter code) if not specified the language is automatically detected

data.name: link
data.description: whether to add external links to identified keywords (optional, requires “disambiguation=1″) 1 – enabled 0 – disabled (default)

data.name: min_weight
data.description: keywords with scores lower than min_weight are filtered (default is 0.25)

data.name: output_format
data.description: desired API output format (optional). Default is json.

data.name: text
data.description: text content to be annotated (required, must be url encoded)

description: An entity annotation based on Wikipedia, available in 5 languages: en, de, fr, es, it.
name: v1
